alysis\nwas employed to characterize the surface nanoclusters. A subpopulation of\nmobile Na$_\\mathrm{v}$1.6 was observed to be transiently trapped in the\nnanoclusters. Somatic Na$_\\mathrm{v}$1.6 nanoclusters represent a new, to our\nknowledge, type of Na$_\\mathrm{v}$ channel localization, and are hypothesized\nto be sites of localized channel regulation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 May 2016 19:24:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Sep 2016 15:15:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-23"}
