 of a new soft\nmode which could lead to instability toward the $K^\\pi=1^-$ octupole shape. A\nwobbling mode of excitation, which is a clear signature of the triviality, is\ndiscussed in terms of a microscopic point of view. A crucial role played by the\nquasiparticle alignment is presented.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 May 2016 09:56:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-06"}
